observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the following courses of actions be made by the Local Chief Executive, to wit:
Direct the LGU Accountant:
1. To secure the monthly account, bank statement from its authorized government depository bank (AGDB) for all their bank accounts maintained and then prepare the corresponding monthly bank reconciliation statements for each bank accounts maintained in accordance with Section 74 of PD No. 1445 and Section 3.2 of COA Circular No. 96-011;
2. To conduct depth review at least at each annual reporting date the account upon recognition of residual value and the useful life of an asset and depreciable amount of each lug’s property, plant and equipment;
3. To prepare a lapsing account “Road Network” schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component of Road Network account at the end of the year;
4. To maintain a subsidiary record particularly Property Ledger Cards (PLC) for property, plant and equipment accounts and Local Road Network Ledger Card for local road network and its components, and
5. To take the necessary adjustments noted in the books of accounts by drawing a Journal Entry Voucher (JEV); and
6. Direct the Local Inventory Committee to continue the conduct of a physical inventory of all equipment belonging to their respective offices; and (2) then to submit a complete Annual Physical Inventory of all property under the agency control as of 31, December, on General Form (41) not later than 31 January of each year;
7. Require the LGU General Services Officer to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map; and
8. Direct the Municipal Engineer to provide the local accountant and the general services officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

We recommended that the concerned LGU top officials make the necessary step for the complete recognition of Local Road Network in the books of accounts as provided in the circular, such as:
a. Conduct an inventory of the local roads under the LGU’s jurisdiction;
b. Maintain the following records/report s: Report of the Local Road Network (RLRN), Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Network (RPCLRN), Local Road Network Ledger Card (LRNLC), and Local Road Network Property Card (LRNPC);
c. Make the necessary adjusting entries in the books upon recognition of Local Road Network account.
